{"q":"Can dependent children get open work permits?","a":"Only in limited circumstances. Many children need visitor or study status instead. Screen age and dependency rules carefully."},{"q":"Should the application be filed together with the principal applicant?","a":"Sometimes. It depends on timing, principal eligibility, documents, and risk. Joint filing can help context but is not always best."},{"q":"How long will the OWP be valid?","a":"Often tied to the principal applicant''s status and passport validity. IRCC decides the final duration."},{"q":"Can the applicant work while waiting?","a":"Only if they already have authorization and meet maintained status rules. Outside-Canada applicants cannot work until approved and admitted with proper status."},{"q":"What if there was a previous spouse OWP refusal?","a":"Order notes if useful, address refusal reasons directly, and strengthen principal eligibility and relationship evidence."},{"q":"Does approval lead to PR?","a":"No. OWP is temporary status. It may support Canadian work experience, but PR requires a separate pathway."},{"q":"What is Description for this service?","a":"Open work permit pathway for eligible spouses, common-law partners, or qualifying dependants linked to a principal applicant''s Canadian work, study, or immigration status."},{"q":"What is Eligible applicants for this service?","a":"Genuine spouse/common-law partner or eligible dependant · Principal applicant has qualifying status · Relationship documents · Funds and admissibility evidence"},{"q":"What is Rule sensitivity for this service?","a":"Eligibility for spouses of students and workers depends on current IRCC categories, program level, occupation, and principal status. Always verify current rules."},{"q":"Important note on Rule sensitivity?","a":"Eligibility for spouses of students and workers depends on current IRCC categories, program level, occupation, and principal status. Always verify current rules."},{"q":"What is Key authority for this service?","a":"Immigration, Refugees and Citizenship Canada (IRCC)"},{"q":"What is After approval for this service?","a":"Applicant may work for most employers in Canada subject to printed conditions. Review expiry alignment with principal applicant status."},{"q":"Is Principal applicant has valid qualifying status in Canada or approved pathway required?","a":"Principal applicant has valid qualifying status in Canada or approved pathway is typically required."},{"q":"Is Applicant is spouse, common-law partner, or qualifying dependant under IRCC rules required?","a":"Applicant is spouse, common-law partner, or qualifying dependant under IRCC rules is typically required."},{"q":"Is Relationship is genuine and well documented required?","a":"Marriage certificate alone may not be enough"},{"q":"Is Principal worker occupation, employer, or permit category qualifies where required required?","a":"Principal worker occupation, employer, or permit category qualifies where required is typically required."},{"q":"Is Principal student program and institution qualify where required required?","a":"Principal student program and institution qualify where required is typically required."},{"q":"Is Applicant passport valid for requested permit period required?","a":"Applicant passport valid for requested permit period is typically required."},{"q":"Is Applicant has no inadmissibility, misrepresentation, or undisclosed refusal issue required?","a":"Applicant has no inadmissibility, misrepresentation, or undisclosed refusal issue is typically required."},{"q":"Is Funds or family support evidence available for settlement and stay required?","a":"Funds or family support evidence available for settlement and stay is typically required."},{"q":"Is Medical exam or biometrics completed if required required?","a":"Assess whether Medical exam or biometrics completed if required is satisfied for this case."},{"q":"What is the Processing time?","a":"3–5m — Varies by applicant location"},