ation."},{"q":"Can the applicant work while waiting?","a":"Only if they already have authorization and meet maintained status rules. Outside-Canada applicants cannot work until approved and admitted with proper status."},{"q":"What if there was a previous spouse OWP refusal?","a":"Order notes if useful, address refusal reasons directly, and strengthen principal eligibility and relationship evidence."},{"q":"Does approval lead to PR?","a":"No. OWP is temporary status. It may support Canadian work experience, but PR requires a separate pathway."},{"q":"What is Description for this service?","a":"Open work permit pathway for eligible spouses, common-law partners, or qualifying dependants linked to a principal applicant''s Canadian work, study, or immigration status."},{"q":"What is Eligible applicants for this service?","a":"Genuine spouse/common-law partner or eligible dependant · Principal applicant has qualifying status · Relationship documents · Funds and admissibility evidence"},{"q":"What is Rule sensitivity for this service?","a":"Eligibility for spouses of students and workers depends on current IRCC categories, program level, occupation, and principal status. Always verify current rules."},{"q":"Important note on Rule sensitivity?","a":"Eligibility for spouses of students and workers depends on current IRCC categories, program level, occupation, and principal status. Always verify current rules."},{"q":"What is Key authority for this service?","a":"Immigration, Refugees and Citizenship Canada (IRCC)"},{"q":"What is After approval for this service?","a":"Applicant may work for most employers in Canada subject to printed conditions. Review expiry alignment with principal applicant status."},{"q":"Is Principal applicant has valid qualifying status in Canada or approved pathway required?","a":"Principal applicant has valid qualifying status in Canada or approved pathway is typically required."},{"q":"Is Applicant is spouse, common-law partner, or qualifying depend